Upload a Quota Dataset to the Revenue Operations Analytics App
If you don’t have Sales Cloud Collaborative Forecasts enabled, you must add quota data to your app. Your quota data must be in a CSV file and contain these fields: StartDate, QuotaAmount, OwnerName, Username.

From the Analytics tab or Analytics Studio, click Browse and find the Quota dataset. In the Quota dataset dropdown menu, select Edit. Click the replace data icon. Locate the CSV file and click Next. If your fiscal period starts on a date other than January 1, update the Quota Metadata file. Save the file.

On the Replace Dataset Data page, locate the Data Schema File area. Click the arrow next to the Quota .JSON file, select Replace File, find the file that you saved and upload it. On the Replace Dataset Data page, click Next. Select the first column —QuotaAmount— and set Field Type to Measure.

Upload your CSV file with the quota data. Rerun the dataflow to update the dashboards. In Data Manager, click Dataflows & Recipes and find your app’s dataflow. Click Run now.
title: Uploading Quota Data to Salesforce CRM Analytics
